{"lemma":"لُدٌّ","slug":"لُدٌّ","root":"#.ل.د","root_slug":"_-ل-د","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ل-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"لُدٌّ","root":"لدد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37664","n37670"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%8F%D8%AF%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37664","headword_ar":"لَدّ","root":"ld","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ladida","text_ar":"لَدِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (second pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ladidota","text_ar":"لَدِدْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", L,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ladadN","text_ar":"لَدَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was violent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement, in contention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altercation; in dispute; in litigation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lad~ahu","text_ar":"لَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, Msb,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lad~N","text_ar":"لَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He overcame him in contention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altercation; in dispute; in litigation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * L, K: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he opposed him violently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemently, in contention,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altercation; in dispute; in litigation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ladidota","text_ar":"لَدِدْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (in some copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ladadota","text_ar":"لَدَدْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laddN","text_ar":"لَددٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IKtt, L: in the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lad~N","text_ar":"لَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou becamest such as is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alad~","text_ar":"اَلَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement, in contention, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IKtt, L, K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lad~ahu Eani AlA^amori","text_ar":"لَدَّهُ عَنِ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lad~N","text_ar":"لَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He restrained, withheld, debarred, hindered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prevented, him from doing the thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K: *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made him to return"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"revert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turned him back"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"away, with gentleness, from the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rad~ahu","text_ar":"رَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (T and L, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rd","text_ar":"رد"},{"kind":"text","text":":) of the dial. of Hudheyl. (L.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lad~ahu","text_ar":"لَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lad~ahu biAll~aduwdi","text_ar":"لَدَّهُ بِاللَّدُودِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lad~N","text_ar":"لَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luduwdN","text_ar":"لُدُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~hu","text_ar":"الدّهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, L, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lad~ahu All~aduwda","text_ar":"لَدَّهُ اللَّدُودَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He administered to him the medicine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"draught, termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laduwd","text_ar":"لَدُود"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, * M, L, K. *) The action termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ad~u","text_ar":"اللَّدُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the taking a child's tongue, and drawing it to one side, and pouring medicine in the other side, between the tongue and the side of the mouth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, L.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lud~a","text_ar":"لُدَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had a medicine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"draught, of the kind termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laduwd","text_ar":"لَدُود"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"administered to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K.) See also 8. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ladadotuhumu Aln~aSiyHapa","text_ar":"لَدَدْتُهُمُ النَّصِيحَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I administered to them sincere,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faithful, advice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"counsel, like as one administers the medicine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"draught, termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laduwd","text_ar":"لَدُود"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.)"}],"source_refs":["L","Msb","S","A","K","M"]},{"entry_id":"n37670","headword_ar":"لَدٌّ","root":"ld","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAd~N","text_ar":"لَادٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sack of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juwaAliq","text_ar":"جُوَالِق"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, L, K:) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labiydN","text_ar":"لَبِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%84%D8%AF/","headword_ar":"لد","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_36","lexicon_en":"Al-Ṣāḥib bin ʿAbbād, Al-Muḥīṭ fī l-Lugha (d. c. 995 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المحيط في اللغة للصاحب بن عباد","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=84501#262ba7","body_html":"<div>لد</div><div>اللذُ: فِعْلُكَ اللَّدُوْدَ حِيْنَ تَلُد به إنساناً؛ وهو دَوَاءٌ يُوْجَرُ في أحَدِ شِقَّيْ فَمِه، والجَميعُ ألِدَّةٌ. واللَّدِيْدَانِ: صَفْقا العُنُقِ من دُوْنِ الأذُنَيْنِ. وجانِبَا كُل شَيْء: لَدِيْدَاه. والتلَددُ: التَّلَفُّتُ باللَّدِيْدَيْنِ. والمُتَلَددُ: العُنُقُ.</div><div>واللَدَدُ: مَصْدَرُ الألَد الشدِيْدِ الخُصوْمَةِ العَسِرِ الانْقِيَادِ، وهو اليَلَنْدَدُ والألَنْدَدُ. ولَدَدْتُ الرَّجُلَ: خَصَمْتَه وغَلَبْتَه.</div><div>ولَدَّه عن كذا: حَبَسَه. وما أجِدُ دُوْنَه مُلْتَدّاً: أي مَعْدِلاً وبُدّاً.</div><div>والْتَدَدْتُ عنه: زِغْتُ.</div><div>وشَدِيْدٌ لَدِيْدٌ: على الإتْبَاعِ.</div><div>ولُد: اسْمُ رَمْلَةٍ بالشأم.</div><div>ولَدَّني فلانٌ: أكْثَرَ مَسْألتيِ. ولَدَّنِي حَقي: مَطَلَنِي ومَنعَنِي.</div>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_49","lexicon_en":"Arabic-English Lexicon by Edward William Lane (d. 1876)","lexicon_ar":"المعجم العربي الإنجليزي لإدوارد وليام لين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=84501#ff7a7c","body_html":"<h3>لد</h3><span class=\"sense\">1</span> لَدّ, originally لَدِدَ, (second <abbr title=\"Persian (Farsi)\">Pers\\.</abbr> لَدِدْتَ, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـَ (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لَدَدٌ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) He was violent, or vehement, in contention, or altercation; in dispute; in litigation. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> لَدَّهُ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـَ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لَدٌّ, (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) He overcame him in contention, or altercation; in dispute; in litigation: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>: *) or he opposed him violently, or vehemently, in contention, or altercation; in dispute; in litigation. (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) لَدِدْتَ, (in some copies of the <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, لَدَدْتَ,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لَددٌ, (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Qaṭṭāʿ al-Ṣiqillī\">IKtt</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>: in the <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, لَدٌّ:) Thou becamest such as is called أَلَدّ [violent, or vehement, in contention, &amp;c.]. (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Qaṭṭāʿ al-Ṣiqillī\">IKtt</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> لَدَّهُ عَنِ الأَمْرِ, (<abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لَدٌّ, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) He restrained, withheld, debarred, hindered, or prevented, him from doing the thing: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>: *) he made him to return or revert, or turned him back or away, with gentleness, from the thing, or affair; like رَدَّهُ: (<abbr title=\"The Tahdhīb of al-Azharī\">T</abbr> and <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, art. رد:) of the <abbr title=\"dialect, لُغَةٌ\">dial.</abbr> of Hudheyl. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> لَدَّهُ, (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) or لَدَّهُ بِاللَّدُودِ, (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـُ (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لَدٌّ and لُدُودٌ; (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) and ↓ الدّهُ; (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) and لَدَّهُ اللَّدُودَ; (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) He administered to him the medicine, or draught, termed لَدُود. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>. *) The action termed اللَّدُّ is the taking a child's tongue, and drawing it to one side, and pouring medicine in the other side, between the tongue and the side of the mouth. (<abbr title=\"al-Farrāʾ\">Fr</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> لُدَّ He had a medicine, or draught, of the kind termed لَدُود administered to him. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) See also 8. <span class=\"sub-sense\">b3:</span> لَدَدْتُهُمُ النَّصِيحَةَ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) I administered to them sincere, or faithful, advice, or counsel, like as one administers the medicine, or draught, termed لَدُود. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) 2 لدّد بِهِ <abbr title=\"idem quod (i.e. the same as)\">i. q.</abbr> ندّد به, (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) i. e., He rendered him notorious, or infamous. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) 3 لادّهُ, <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> لِدَادٌ (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>) and مُلَادَّةٌ, (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>,) He contended with him violently, or vehemently, in an altercation; in a dispute; in a litigation. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> مَا زِلْتُ أُلَادُّ عَنْكَ I ceased not to repel from thee; or, to defend thee. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>.) 4 الدّهُ He found him to be such as is called أَلَدّ [violent, or vehement, in contention, &amp;c]. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> الدّ بِهِ He opposed him in contention, or altercation; in dispute; in litigation. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) See also 1 and 3.<span class=\"sense\">5</span> تلدّد (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) He turned his face to the right and left, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) in confusion, perplexity, or amazement: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) from اللَّدِيدَانِ signifying “ the two sides ” of the neck. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> He tarried, or waited, in expectation. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) 8 التدّ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) and التدّ لَدُودًا, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) He swallowed a medicine, or draught, of the kind termed لَدُود. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) See also لُدّض.<br><br><span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> التدّ عَنْهُ He declined from him, or it. (<abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) لَدٌّ: see لَادٌّ. <span class=\"sub-sense\">b2:</span> A [sack of the kind called]<br><br>جُوَالِق: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) like لَبِيدٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) لَدُودٌ: see لَادٌّ.<br><br><span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> لَدُودٌ and ↓ لَدِيدٌ A medicine (or draught, <abbr title=\"al-Aṣmaʿī\">As</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>) that is poured into one of the two sides of the mouth (<abbr title=\"al-Aṣmaʿī\">As</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) by means of the instrument called مُسْعُط: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> أَلِدَّةٌ: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) from اللَّدِيدَانِ signifying <br><br>“ the two sides ” of a valley. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) It is said in a proverb, جَرَى مِنْهُ مَجْرَى اللَّدُودِ [It acted upon him, or affected him, like the medicine, or draught, termed لَدُود; i. e., unpleasantly, or disagreeably]. (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Sikkīt\">ISk</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>.) See Freytag's Arab. <abbr title=\"proverb, مَثَلٌ\">Prov.</abbr> i. 282 لَدِيدٌ: see لَدُودٌ.<br><br><span class=\"sub-sense\">A2:</span> لَدِيدَانِ The two sides of a valley: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) each of them is called لَدِيدٌ: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) and the two sides of the neck, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) below the ears: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) or the two lateral muscles of the neck: (<abbr title=\"The Muḥkam of Ibn Sīdah\">M</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) the two sides of the mouth: (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) and of the penis: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) and (as some say, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>) of anything: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> أَلِدَّةٌ: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) and لَدِيدٌ, <abbr title=\"according\">accord.</abbr> to <abbr title=\"Abū ʿAmr b. al-ʿAlāʾ and Abū ʿAmr al-Shaybānī\">AA</abbr>, signifies the outside of the neck. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) <span class=\"sub-sense\">A3:</span> See لَادٌّ.<br><br>لَادٌّ and ↓ لَدُودٌ, (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) the latter having an intensive sense, and ↓ لَدٌّ, which is an <abbr title=\"infinitive noun, مَصْدَرٌ\">inf. n.</abbr> used as an <abbr title=\"نَعْتٌ and وَصْفٌ and صِفَةٌ\">epithet</abbr> [and therefore also intensive], (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) A man who overcomes in contention, or altercation; in dispute; in litigation: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, * <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>: *) or, who opposes violently, or vehemently, and very violently, or vehemently, in contention, or altercation; in dispute; in litigation: (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>:) and ↓ أَلَدُّ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and ↓ أَلَنْدَدٌ and ↓ يَلَنْدَدٌ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) a man violent, or vehement, in contention, or altercation; in dispute; in litigation: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>:) or difficult therein, and vehement in war: (<abbr title=\"Ibn al-Qaṭṭāʿ al-Ṣiqillī\">IKtt</abbr>:) or a contentious, disputatious, or litigious, (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>,) and tenacious adversary, who will not incline to the truth: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) the <abbr title=\"feminine, مؤَنَّثٌ\">fem.</abbr> of ↓ ألَدُّ is لَدَّآءُ: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>:) and the pl, لُدٌّ (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) and لِدَادٌ: (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) the أ in ↓ أَلَنْدَدٌ and the ى in ↓ يَلَنْدَدٌ are letters of quasi-coördination, [i. e., added to render those two words <abbr title=\"مُلْحَقٌ\">quasi-coordinate</abbr> to سَفَرْجَلٌ,] as is shown by the two dáls being not incorporated by idghám; for it is allowable to add a letter at the beginning of a word for the purpose of quasi-coördination when the word has another augmentative letter: (<abbr title=\"Ibn Jinnī\">IJ</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>:) the <abbr title=\"diminutive, مُصَغَّرٌ\">dim.</abbr> of ↓ أَلنْدَدٌ is ↓ أُلَيْدُّ, because it is originally أَلَدُّ, the ن being added to render it quasi-coördinate to سَفَرْجَلٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) قَوْمًا لُدًّا in the <abbr title=\"The Quran\">Kur</abbr>, [xix. 97,] is said to signify A people who are adversaries perverted from the truth: or, who are deaf to the truth. (<abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.) You say also, هُوَ شَدِيدٌ لَدِيدٌ [assimilating the second <abbr title=\"نَعْتٌ and وَصْفٌ and صِفَةٌ\">epithet</abbr> in form to the first, He is strong, and one who overcomes in contention, &amp;c.] (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) أَلَدُّ and أَلَنْدَدٌ and يَلَنْدَدٌ and أُلَيْدُّ: see لَادٌّ.<br><br>مَلْدُودٌ A man who has had a medicine, or draught, of the kind termed لَدُود administered to him. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) المُتَلَدَّدُ (<abbr title=\"مَجَازٌ and مَجَازِيٌّ\">tropical</abbr>:) The neck. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) مَا لِى عَنْهُ مُلْتَدٌّ I have no way of avoiding, or escaping, it: (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>:) as also مُحْتَدٌّ. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Lisān al-ʿArab of Ibn Manẓur\">L</abbr>.)"}]}}